<p>I Piece. In Telugu characters</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/>Sāma Jīyya
<lb n="2" break="no"/>la koḍuku Ā
<lb n="3" break="no"/>kana maṇḍapaṁ
<lb n="4"/>Āppaḷike rāyi
<lb n="5"/>parapiṁchchēnu
</p>

<p>II Piece.</p>

<p>In Nāgari and Grantha characters</p>

<p>
<lb n="2"/><seg rendition="class:nāgarī maturity:undetermined">1 <g type="danda">.</g> śrīparvatanivāsa śrīvibhūtigau </seg>
<lb n="3" break="no"/><seg rendition="class:nāgarī maturity:undetermined">2 <g type="danda">.</g> raya śaraṇārthi <g type="ddanda">.</g> </seg> <hi rend="grantha">śrīpa</hi>
<lb n="3" break="no"/><hi rend="grantha">rvvatanivāsa śrīvi</hi>
<lb n="4" break="no"/><hi rend="grantha">bhūti gauraya śaraṇā</hi>
<lb n="5" break="no"/><hi rend="grantha"><unclear>rdhi</unclear> §</hi>
</p>

<p>III Piece</p>

<p>In Telugu characters</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/><unclear>Sāmrākka</unclear> Gauraya-rūpam <unclear>nē</unclear>
<lb n="2" break="no"/><unclear>lu</unclear> Kāruṇya vidēmu kru
<lb n="3" break="no"/>pa sēsidi <g type="ddanda">.</g>
</p>

<p>In Nāgari. To the proper left [of?] a figure with folded hands</p>

<p>
<lb n="0"/><seg rendition="class:nāgarī maturity:undetermined">gaurayarūpamu</seg>
</p>

<p>In Grantha. To the proper left [of?] a figure with folded hands</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/><hi rend="grantha">gauraya</hi>
<lb n="2"/><hi rend="grantha">rūpamu</hi> 
</p>

<p>IV Piece In Telugu characters</p>

<p>
<lb n="1"/>Śrī-yoruṁṭyaṁtika
<lb n="2"/><unclear>Pūvī</unclear> rāju 1 palijani śri-giṭi
<lb n="3" break="no"/>śyāga-vāsi 1 śrī-Paṁḍitārā
<lb n="4" break="no"/><unclear>dhya</unclear> gṛihasya dāsō <g type="danda">.</g> Vibhūti
<lb n="5" break="no"/>gaurḥ śaraṇāgatō vaḥ ll
<lb n="6"/>maṁgala-mahā-śrī-śrī śrī
